Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.36,0:02:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just get me home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.96,0:02:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just get me home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, hello, this is David Linn\Nfrom {\i1}The New York Times.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,May I speak with Susan,\Nplease? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Susan, it's David again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just calling to see if we can set--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes. Well, I figured\Nwe'd have to do the interview by phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,since they've already left New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we'd really love to get\Nis a photo of Mr. and Mrs. Schwartz
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to go along with the article.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.44,0:05:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When are they scheduled\Nto get home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so they'll be home\Ntonight. Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.48,0:06:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the address I have on them\Nis Upper Canyon Road. Is that still...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it isn't. They've--\NOh, let me get a pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.96,0:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do they...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.08,0:06:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Tesuque. I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the address?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.32,0:06:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that up near the opera house?\NI hear that's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be in contact\Nwith my photographer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.08,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to check on his schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, it's their call.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.08,0:06:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how busy\NMr. and Mrs. Schwartz are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.16,0:06:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This should make one hell of a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.20,0:06:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.56,0:06:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm just saying,\Nit's apples and oranges.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I maintain,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if I want pizza,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.64,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to a pizza place.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.60,0:07:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If I want Thai,\NI go to a Thai place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the point in comparing\NDid I marry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.96,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,pizza to Thai?\NWhat has happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.40,0:07:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is different.\N- They're completely--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.68,0:07:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on,\Nare you the man I married?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the guy who wants to end\Nthis ridiculous conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.40,0:07:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,kick off my shoes, and have\Na very large glass of wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.04,0:07:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm gonna tell you\Nto be my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.12,0:07:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.32,0:07:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because it has history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.20,0:07:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Prohibition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}Sweet Smell of Success.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And Per Se has Thomas Keller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Game, set, and match.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.76,0:07:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole vibe is so Yountville.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You transplant it to Manhattan--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:07:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Transplant it to Islamabad,\NI would eat there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.84,0:08:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's a good thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What, Islamabad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.68,0:08:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Napa. We have to go to Napa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, all this talk of food.\NDo you think Juana left us anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.20,0:08:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't think we're coming back\Nuntil Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you told her.\NNo, I haven't talked to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.52,0:08:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a pear, that'll be perfect.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna get us\Na nice bottle of wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.32,0:08:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think we have any of those--?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.52,0:08:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those crackers with,\Nlike, the sun-dried tomato,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were slightly peppery,\Nbut not too peppery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- We don't have them?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.92,0:08:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask Juana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.20,0:08:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't had them in forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.60,0:08:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why she doesn't get those.\NWhy don't you talk to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got that thing with her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.68,0:08:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Napa?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How long since we've been?\NTwo years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, that's two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.36,0:08:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, too long, right?\NIs this okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.80,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that looks {\i1}p e r fe c to.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:08:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna get the fireplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.84,0:09:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it good?\NMm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it ripe?\NMm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.08,0:09:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We could invite George and Delores.\NThey could come up from Marin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.08,0:09:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Bill and Miriam Cohen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have a little\Nspa action, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we could do\Nsome sort of wine, and then--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Gretchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.20,0:09:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Elliott.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I really like your new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Walt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.24,0:09:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we looking east?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My God, you must have one great view\Nof the Sangre de Cristos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Walt,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.24,0:10:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw you on {\i1}Charlie Rose.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You looked great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.16,0:10:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You both did.\NIf you are here to--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.12,0:10:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To hurt us--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Walt, whatever it is\Nyou're planning--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'm here\Nto give you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.08,0:10:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the three of us take a walk\Nto it? It's just parked down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.48,0:10:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get it past your gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Elliott, if we're gonna go that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.80,0:10:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll need a bigger knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep stacking. It'll all fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.96,0:11:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just throw it on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.28,0:11:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Gretchen, would you mind? We don't\Nwant to lose any under the furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.52,0:11:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That is $9,720,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did it come from?\NAnd why is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I earned it, and you're going to\Ngive it to my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why?\NWalt, I don't think we--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,On my son's 18th birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which is 10 months\Nand two days from today,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you will give him this money,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.32,0:11:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of an irrevocable trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.60,0:11:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You will tell him that it is his\Nto do with as he sees fit,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:12:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the hope that he uses it\Nfor his college education.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.68,0:12:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the betterment of his family.\NWalt, I'm not sure that we follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.96,0:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, why, in particular,\Nwould we--?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.48,0:12:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wanna give your kids\Ndrug money, go do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and son hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.72,0:12:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't take my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.44,0:12:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they did,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.12,0:12:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the federal government\Nwouldn't let them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But two rich benefactors who are known\Nfor their charitable endeavors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who would think nothing of,\Nfor instance, writing a $28 million check,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.76,0:12:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to help victims\Nof methamphetamine abuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to think that your money\Nwould be very welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.96,0:12:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't make any sense\Ncoming from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.40,0:12:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.28,0:12:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My children are blameless victims\Nof their monstrous father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A man who you once knew\Nquite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it a beau geste,\Ncall it liberal guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,call it whatever you want, but do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are not to spend\Na single dime of your own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If there are taxes or lawyers' fees owed,\Nyou will take it right from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They use my money, never yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Walt, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.12,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens next?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we shake on it,\Nand I leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.44,0:14:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I can trust you to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.04,0:14:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.56,0:14:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely, you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move. Don't--\NDon't dare move a muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.48,0:14:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want them to think that\Nyou're trying to get away. Just breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.20,0:14:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just this afternoon,\NI had an extra $200,000
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that I would have loved dearly\Nto leave on top of this table.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.60,0:14:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I gave it to the two best\Nhit men west of the Mississippi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever happens to me tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll still be out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping tabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And if,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for any reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.44,0:15:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that my children\Ndo not get this money,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a kind of countdown\Nwill begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a day or so later,\Nmaybe a week, a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.04,0:15:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're going for a walk in Santa\NFe or Manhattan or Prague, wherever,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're talking\Nabout your stock prices
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.44,0:15:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,without a worry in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.68,0:15:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll hear the scrape\Nof a footstep behind you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but before you can\Neven turn around:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.76,0:15:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.64,0:15:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.68,0:16:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, beautiful people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where you get to make it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.48,0:17:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.56,0:17:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I don't exactly know\Nhow to feel about all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For real, yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole thing felt kind of shady,\Nyou know, like, morality-wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.84,0:17:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.72,0:17:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Better.\NYeah, definitely improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.72,0:17:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this I hear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about blue meth\Nstill being out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.64,0:17:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.88,0:17:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.76,0:17:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it still being sold?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.28,0:17:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.96,0:17:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, aren't you\Nstill cooking?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.08,0:18:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.44,0:18:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We were sure it was you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.20,0:18:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because that shit is choice, yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.72,0:18:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Better than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, um, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.80,0:18:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesse.\NSeriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You said he moved to Alaska.\NThat's what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.80,0:18:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on, Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Passing the torch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, man, couldn't he at least\Nthrow a brother a bone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.44,0:20:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, what happened there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.12,0:20:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.64,0:20:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Well, happy birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.28,0:21:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy money. Till we catch you. Say\Nthe word, I'll take you on a ride-along.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.68,0:21:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can watch us\Nknock down a meth lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.52,0:21:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a little excitement\Nin your life. Heh, heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.52,0:21:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome. Would you like a menu?\NNo, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamomile tea with soy milk, please.\NAll right, you got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.92,0:22:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.32,0:22:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.08,0:22:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How's things?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.60,0:22:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I like your...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.52,0:22:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My blouse?\NNice. Yeah, I like the color.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.00,0:22:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a nice color on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.00,0:22:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's kind of a--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.68,0:22:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know exactly what you'd call it.\NIt's kind of a cornflower blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.60,0:22:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you say or do anything,\Njust hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.48,0:22:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Todd.\NNobody knows that I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.52,0:22:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just listen for two minutes,\Nand then I'll leave. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.08,0:22:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.72,0:22:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just two minutes of your time.\NThat's all I ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.28,0:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.64,0:22:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're running out of\Nmethylamine, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.28,0:23:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.64,0:23:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been at it long enough.\NYou must be running low.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.12,0:23:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a new method
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.16,0:23:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that requires no methylamine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy, and it will keep you in business.\NAnd, Todd, I could teach it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.08,0:23:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know\Nto find us here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.32,0:23:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.00,0:23:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Tuesday morning,\Nyou and I met here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.32,0:23:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're rather\Nschedule-oriented, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.12,0:23:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.56,0:23:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I need the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.40,0:23:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spent almost all of mine already,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.16,0:24:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,just trying to stay\None step ahead of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. White, I don't think there's--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How much would it cost us?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.00,0:24:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing short of a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.92,0:24:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And believe me, for this,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.28,0:24:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that is giving it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.20,0:24:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Jack should hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.08,0:24:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.60,0:24:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, listen, I can come up\Nthere tonight and talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.88,0:24:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.80,0:24:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a win-win situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.40,0:24:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, what can I get for you two?\NHe's just leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.44,0:24:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Good seeing you again.\NTake care.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.76,0:24:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.44,0:24:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.68,0:24:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I need more stevia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:24:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, no disrespect to the man,\Nbut doing business with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.04,0:24:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, that's not--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.24,0:25:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we're not\Ndoing business with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.56,0:25:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Todd, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.32,0:25:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me walk you through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.60,0:25:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus. Did you look at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.40,0:25:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be doing him a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.60,0:27:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hello, please record after the tone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.48,0:27:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Truce, all right?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.40,0:27:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Skyler, I have news about Walt,\Nand you need to hear it,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.64,0:27:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}so if you're there, pick up.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.92,0:27:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Skyler--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.48,0:27:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.96,0:27:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.88,0:27:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Walt's in town.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.32,0:27:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.52,0:27:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That car they thought he stole\Nin New Hampshire,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.28,0:27:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they found it in a Denny's\Nparking lot right on Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.64,0:27:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And your next-door neighbor,\Non the right-- What's her name, Becky?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.28,0:27:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Becky's on the left. Carol's on the right.\N{\i1}Becky, Carol, whatever.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.00,0:27:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She saw him at your old house.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.68,0:27:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just this morning, plain as day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.00,0:27:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's there, walking out of your house,\Nand he calls her by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.72,0:27:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't hurt her, did he? He didn't--?\NNo, he's just like, "Hey, Becky!"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.32,0:27:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or Carol, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.20,0:28:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She said he looked exactly\Nlike the Unabomber.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.80,0:28:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's positive it was him.\NThey're getting calls from all over town.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.72,0:28:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here, he's there,\Nhe's going to blow up city hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.84,0:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He has some sort of manifesto.\NHe wants to be on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.08,0:28:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's making these calls? Him?\N{\i1}There are two or three voices.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.72,0:28:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're not sure if they're crank calls\Nor people he's put up to it,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.56,0:28:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or if they're actual anonymous tips.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.80,0:28:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's stretching them thin,\Nwhich is maybe the point.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.80,0:28:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As far as I'm concerned,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.32,0:28:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there are three places that he would go:\NTo you, to me, or Flynn.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.40,0:28:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.12,0:28:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They're watching the high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.04,0:28:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably watching\Nyour place too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.48,0:28:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.80,0:28:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that's what Hank would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no way Walt's getting to you.\NThey are absolutely going to catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.32,0:28:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.60,0:28:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That arrogant asshole thinks he's some\Ncriminal mastermind, but he's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.12,0:28:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But on the off chance...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.20,0:28:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.28,0:29:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,On the million-to-one chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.28,0:29:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you be on the lookout, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.44,0:29:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.92,0:29:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.20,0:29:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.28,0:29:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.04,0:29:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't kill anybody\Nsneaking in here, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.36,0:29:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't hurt anybody?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.68,0:30:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.52,0:30:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You look terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.40,0:30:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.52,0:30:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But I feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.92,0:30:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.36,0:30:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.56,0:30:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I needed\Na proper goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.08,0:30:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not our last phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.88,0:30:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.88,0:30:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be coming to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.80,0:30:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in custody,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.32,0:31:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what stops those people\Nfrom coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.36,0:31:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When--
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.08,0:31:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When I still had the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.72,0:31:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,three men came\Nin the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.40,0:31:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,wearing masks, threatening\NHolly and Flynn and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.32,0:31:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They told me not to talk about\Nthat woman at the car wash,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.68,0:31:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're in custody--
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.64,0:31:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not coming back.\NNot after tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.60,0:31:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.48,0:31:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want your money, Walt.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.84,0:31:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought Flynn made that clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.28,0:31:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.48,0:31:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't have any to give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.72,0:31:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent the last of it getting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.12,0:31:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.76,0:31:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.72,0:32:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the DEA once I leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.04,0:32:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them I was here.\NThat I forced my way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.40,0:32:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.92,0:32:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them I wanted\Nbacon and eggs on my birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.04,0:32:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I gave you that ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.52,0:32:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those numbers\Nare GPS coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.48,0:32:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.32,0:32:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A burial site.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.40,0:32:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where they'll\Nfind Hank and Steve Gomez.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.16,0:32:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where I buried our money.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.80,0:32:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the men who stole it from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.52,0:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the men who still have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.48,0:32:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they murdered Hank and Steve
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.88,0:32:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and put them in that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.40,0:33:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you trade that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.72,0:33:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for a deal with the prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.32,0:33:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You get yourself out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.16,0:33:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Skyler.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.76,0:33:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Skyler.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.56,0:33:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.40,0:33:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to understand--\NIf I have to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.24,0:33:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one more time
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you did this for the family--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.72,0:33:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.48,0:33:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.36,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.64,0:33:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.80,0:33:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,really...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.52,0:34:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.68,0:34:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Flynn will be home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.08,0:34:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I go,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.60,0:34:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,may I see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.44,0:37:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.68,0:37:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, man, this thing's a classic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.04,0:37:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What block you got in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.44,0:37:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The 500 or the 425?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.20,0:37:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.04,0:37:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.28,0:37:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Five hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.92,0:37:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.20,0:38:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No replacement for displacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.64,0:38:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.24,0:38:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To the clubhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.36,0:38:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead, just park it\Nright in front over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.44,0:38:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, just straight in, man.\NJust-- What are--?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.16,0:38:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, fine, here, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.72,0:38:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.12,0:39:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn around,\Nput your arms out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.92,0:39:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,While you're at it,\Nwhy don't you lift your shirt up,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.92,0:39:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,give us a spin?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.56,0:39:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, I'm not wearing a wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.68,0:39:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.96,0:39:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My wallet and keys?\NYeah, you'll get them back. Just relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.92,0:40:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.52,0:40:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes open.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.32,0:40:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, look at you with\Nthat head of hair. Is that real?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.00,0:40:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.60,0:40:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a wig? Seriously?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.00,0:40:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing before,\Nshaving it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.48,0:40:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.68,0:40:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, that is one fine\Nhead of hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.68,0:40:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, otherwise,\Nyou look like shit, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.16,0:40:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello to you too, Jack.\NNow, can we talk business?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.80,0:40:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.88,0:40:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Todd tell you what I'm offering?\NYeah, he told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.28,0:40:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is\Nwe're not really in the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.36,0:40:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're low on methylamine.\NWhat happens then?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.32,0:40:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll get more.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.68,0:40:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That Quayle woman's got her own setup.\NThe heat's off her.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.24,0:40:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She can break loose a barrel.\NIt ain't broke, so why fix it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.72,0:41:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Todd, please, would you\Nexplain things to your uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.64,0:41:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain to him the benefit\Nof what I'm offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.80,0:41:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You really shouldn't\Nhave come back, Mr. White.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.84,0:41:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.48,0:41:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Jack.\NWhere do you want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.96,0:41:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,\Nanywhere but my living room?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.48,0:41:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him out back.\NJack, look, you owe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.32,0:41:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You owe me.\NHey, hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.88,0:41:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.\NI owe you, what for?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.64,0:41:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesse Pinkman. You promised\Nyou would kill him, and you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.20,0:41:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you partnered with him.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.68,0:41:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're his partner now--\NWhoa, stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.76,0:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Partners? What are you\Ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.96,0:41:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.60,0:41:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's cooking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.76,0:41:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What, are you gonna lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.48,0:41:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Him being alive\Nis not him and me being partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.56,0:41:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by a damn sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.48,0:41:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What, you think\NI'd partner with a rat?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.40,0:42:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is that little piece of shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.08,0:42:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's finishing up a batch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.64,0:42:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Go get him. Bring him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.20,0:42:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle Jack--\NNo. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.72,0:42:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This one here, calling me a liar?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.20,0:42:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He just insulted you,\Nhe insulted me, all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.28,0:42:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus. Hustle it up. Come on.\NLet's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.52,0:42:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna show you\Njust how wrong you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.24,0:42:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm putting that bullet\Nin your head myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.60,0:43:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you see what I'm\Ntalking about, you son of a bitch?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.80,0:43:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, does this look\Nlike a partner to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.96,0:43:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here. Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.88,0:43:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.72,0:43:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.56,0:43:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a gander.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.28,0:43:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.08,0:43:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, partner? Right, buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.44,0:44:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardworking, good partner.\NFifty-fifty partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.28,0:44:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hurry this shit up?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.80,0:44:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it quick?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.76,0:44:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Toddy, get him off, would you?\NYeah, Toddy, get them both off.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.64,0:45:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.52,0:45:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.96,0:46:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. White.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.12,0:47:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.64,0:47:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You want your money, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.72,0:47:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna know where it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.32,0:47:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull that trigger, you'll never--
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.68,0:48:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.72,0:48:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.00,0:48:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Say the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.76,0:48:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Say you want this!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.84,0:48:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happens until I hear you say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.84,0:48:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.80,0:49:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.60,0:49:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick up the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.08,0:49:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hello?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.12,0:49:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.36,0:49:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.12,0:50:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah, it's done.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.48,0:50:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's gone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.04,0:50:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're all gone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.48,0:50:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Todd? Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.48,0:50:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Walt.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.24,0:50:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.64,0:50:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind of under the weather?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.04,0:50:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you've got the flu?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.92,0:50:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be\Nthe ricin I gave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.76,0:50:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I slipped it into that stevia crap\Nthat you're always putting in your tea.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.00,0:50:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.00,0:50:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.00,0:50:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,goodbye, Lydia.
